Jetson Nano – Node-RED + Git Deployment Guide

1. System Overview
Development nodes (Raspberry Pis)
Run Node‑RED, 
Developers modify flows and configs
Changes are pushed to GitHub
Deployment node (Jetson Nano)
Pulls configuration from GitHub
Runs Node‑RED as a system service


2. Jetson Nano Base Setup
2.1 OS
Ubuntu (JetPack / L4T based)
2.2  terminal with usb- c type
ls /dev/ttyACM* take the output from this 
sudo minicom -D /dev/ttyACM0 -b 115200

2.3 Network
Wi‑Fi configured via nmcli
Internet access verified before continuing

3. Node.js & Node‑RED
3.1 Node Versions
Node.js: v20.x
Node‑RED: v4.x
This combination is required because Node‑RED v4 does not support Node.js 18.
For installation :bash <(curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/node-red/linux-installers/master/deb/update-nodejs-and-nodered) 
3.2 Node‑RED Installation
Node‑RED is installed using the official Linux installer:
Installed system‑wide
Runs as a systemd service
Autostarts on boot
3.3 Service Commands
node-red-start     # start service
node-red-stop      # stop service
node-red-restart   # restart service
node-red-log       # view logs


